Sceloporus orcutti is a species of lizard native to southwestern North America.
They have a slender body and a short, spiky tail.
Their coloration varies, but they are typically gray or brown with black stripes or bars.
They have small scales along their back and sides and larger scales on their belly.
Their eyes are large and round and they have a pointed snout.
Sceloporus orcutti can be found in a variety of habitats, including deserts, scrublands, and rocky terrain.
They are known for their ability to quickly scurry and hide when threatened.
